        "subgoalLabel": "State the problem",
        "instruction": "Find 234 × 45.",
        "work": "  234\n×  45\n-----",
        "explanation": "Use the standard algorithm: multiply by ones, multiply by tens, then add."
      },
      {
        "subgoalLabel": "Multiply by the ones digit",
        "instruction": "Find 234 × 5.",
        "work": "4×5=20 (write 0, carry 2). 3×5=15+2=17 (write 7, carry 1). 2×5=10+1=11. First partial product: 1,170.",
        "explanation": "Work right to left through each digit of 234."
      },
      {
        "subgoalLabel": "Multiply by the tens digit",
        "instruction": "Find 234 × 40.",
        "work": "Write 0 placeholder. 4×4=16 (write 6, carry 1). 3×4=12+1=13 (write 3, carry 1). 2×4=8+1=9. Second partial product: 9,360.",
        "explanation": "Place a 0 in the ones column, then multiply 234 by 4."
      },
      {
        "subgoalLabel": "Add the partial products",
        "instruction": "Add 1,170 + 9,360.",
        "work": "1,170 + 9,360 = 10,530.",
        "explanation": "The sum gives the final product."
      },
      {
        "subgoalLabel": "State the answer",
        "instruction": "What is 234 × 45?",
        "work": "234 × 45 = 10,530",
        "explanation": "The same two-step process works for any multi-digit × 2-digit multiplication."
      }
    ]
